{
  "local_port": 39544,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I learn Spanish in Delhi?",
  "response": "Delhi offers several options for learning Spanish, ranging from language institutes to online platforms. Here are some of the top places and methods to learn Spanish in Delhi:\n\n### 1. **Language Institutes**\n   - **Instituto Cervantes, New Delhi**  \n     - **Location:** 48, Hanuman Road, Connaught Place  \n     - **Details:** Instituto Cervantes is the official Spanish language and cultural center, offering structured courses for all levels. They provide both in-person and online classes.\n     - **Website:** [www.delhi.cervantes.es](https://delhi.cervantes.es)\n   \n   - **Language Next**  \n     - **Location:** D-212, Ground Floor, Defence Colony  \n     - **Details:** Offers beginner to advanced Spanish courses. They also provide customized corporate training and private tuitions.\n     - **Website:** [www.languagenext.com](http://www.languagenext.com)\n\n   - **Krosslink Academy**  \n     - **Location:** Lajpat Nagar and other locations  \n     - **Details:** Known for its interactive teaching methods, Krosslink offers Spanish courses for various proficiency levels.\n     - **Website:** [www.krosslink.com](http://www.krosslink.com)\n\n   - **Vidya Integration and Language Institute**  \n     - **Location:** South Extension, Karol Bagh, and other areas  \n     - **Details:** Offers affordable Spanish courses with experienced teachers.\n     - **Website:** [www.vidyaintegration.com](http://www.vidyaintegration.com)\n\n### 2. **University Language Departments**\n   - **Jawaharlal Nehru University (JNU)**  \n     - **Location:** JNU Campus  \n     - **Details:** Offers Spanish courses as part of its foreign language programs for students and professionals.\n\n   - **University of Delhi (DU)**  \n     - **Location:** Various colleges like St. Stephen\u2019s College, Lady Shri Ram College, etc.  \n     - **Details:** Some colleges under DU offer Spanish as an optional or elective subject.\n\n### 3. **Online Platforms**\n   - **Duolingo**, **Babbel**, and **Rosetta Stone**  \n     - **Details:** These apps are great for beginners and offer flexible learning schedules.\n\n   - **Preply** and **Italki**  \n     - **Details:** Connect with native Spanish tutors for personalized online lessons.\n\n### 4. **Private Tutors**\n   - **UrbanPro**, **LearnPick**, and other online platforms  \n     - **Details:** Find certified Spanish tutors in Delhi for one-on-one or group classes.\n\n### 5. **Language Exchange Meetups**\n   - **Meetup.com** and **Couchsurfing**  \n     - **Details:** Join language exchange groups in Delhi to practice Spanish with native speakers and fellow learners.\n\nBefore enrolling, consider your goals, budget, and preferred learning style. Many institutes offer trial classes or demo sessions to help you decide. \u00a1Buena suerte! (Good luck!)",
  "temperature": 1.0,
